National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has asked the Federal Government to put a huge question mark in the planned increase in Value Added Tax, saying it will be an attempt to further tax the ordinary man in the country. Tinubu who spoke at the 11th Bola Tinubu Colloquium to mark his birthday in Abuja said government should widen the tax NWT and ensure all those Nigerians who have refused to pay their tax are made to do so as a way of raising revenue for government.
